@{b}GClock@{ub}


Analogous clock program. Displays time, date and DCF77 receiver state. Try it.


@ENDNODE

@NODE TimeSignal
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}TimeSignal@{ub}


Acoustic time signal.


For example try the following tool types entries:
@{LINDENT 3}


MINUTES=1

BACKGROUND=Background_Audio

VOLUME3=55

FREQUENCY2=1353

START_BACKGROUND_SEC=50

START_SEC=57

AUDIO_FILTER=OFF


And if you don't have a radio clock or DCF77 is not running:

CHECK_DCF77=NO


@{LINDENT 1}

@{"TimeSignal - Tool Types" LINK "TimeSignal - Tool Types"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - Characteristics"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}TimeSignal  -  Characteristics@{ub}


Sorry, nothing here yet.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - Tool Types"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}


Tooltypes for TimeSignal:


@{" MINUTES " LINK "TimeSignal - MINUTES" 0}

@{" BEEP1 " LINK "TimeSignal - BEEP" 0}

@{" BEEP2 " LINK "TimeSignal - BEEP" 0}

@{" BACKGROUND " LINK "TimeSignal - BACKGROUND" 0}

@{" VOLUME1 " LINK "TimeSignal - VOLUMES" 0}

@{" VOLUME2 " LINK "TimeSignal - VOLUMES" 0}

@{" VOLUME3 " LINK "TimeSignal - VOLUMES" 0}

@{" AUDIO_FILTER " LINK "TimeSignal - AUDIO_FILTER" 0}

@{" START_BACKGROUND_SEC " LINK "TimeSignal - START_BACKGROUND_SEC" 0}

@{" START_SEC " LINK "TimeSignal - START_SEC" 0}

@{" ONE_TIME " LINK "TimeSignal - ONE_TIME" 0}

@{" FREQUENCY1 " LINK "TimeSignal - FREQUENCY" 0}

@{" FREQUENCY2 " LINK "TimeSignal - FREQUENCY" 0}

@{" DURATION1 " LINK "TimeSignal - DURATION" 0}

@{" DURATION2 " LINK "TimeSignal - DURATION" 0}

@{" CHECK_DCF77 " LINK "TimeSignal - CHECK_DCF77" 0}

@{" TASK_PRIORITY " LINK "TimeSignal - TASK_PRIORITY" 0}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - MINUTES"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}MINUTES@{ub}                     Default:  MINUTES=60


Difference between time signals.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - BEEP"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}BEEP1@{ub}                       Default:  (BEEP1)

@{b}BEEP2@{ub}                       Default:  (BEEP2)


Optional audio samples.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - BACKGROUND"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}BACKGROUND@{ub}                  Default:  (BACKGROUND)


Optional audio sample for Background.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - VOLUMES"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}VOLUME1@{ub}                     Default:  VOLUME1=64

@{b}VOLUME2@{ub}                               VOLUME2=64

@{b}VOLUME3@{ub}                               VOLUME3=50


0 (no sound) ... 64 (maximum volume)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - AUDIO_FILTER"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}AUDIO_FILTER@{ub}                Default:  AUDIO_FILTER=ON


AUDIO_FILTER=OFF causes TimeSignal to switch off the Amiga audio filter while playing.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - START_BACKGROUND_SEC"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}START_BACKGROUND_SEC@{ub}        Default:  START_BACKGROUND_SEC=50


Start second of background audio sample selected with @{" BACKGROUND " LINK "TimeSignal - BACKGROUND" 0}.


Value must be 19 to 55 and less than @{" START_SEC " LINK "TimeSignal - START_SEC" 0}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - START_SEC"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}START_SEC@{ub}                   Default:  START_SEC=56


First second of time signal.


Value must be greater
than @{" START_BACKGROUND_SEC " LINK "TimeSignal - START_BACKGROUND_SEC" 0}.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - ONE_TIME"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}ONE_TIME@{ub}                    Default:  ONE_TIME=NO


NO:  Only one time signal.


YES: Continuously.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - FREQUENCY"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}FREQUENCY1@{ub}                  Default:  FREQUENCY1=1000

@{b}FREQUENCY2@{ub}                  Default:  FREQUENCY2=1000


Frequency for internal generated sound (in Hertz).


If samples used for BEEP1 or BEEP2 then FREQUENCY1 or FREQUENCY2 are ignored.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - DURATION"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}DURATION1@{ub}                   Default:  DURATION1=100

@{b}DURATION2@{ub}                   Default:  DURATION2=1000


Duration (in ms) of internal generated sounds.


The maximum of DURATION1 is 999.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - CHECK_DCF77"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}CHECK_DCF77@{ub}                 Default:  CHECK_DCF77=YES


YES: TimeSignal works only if DCF77 has received the time.


NO:  TimeSignal ignores DCF77.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "TimeSignal - TASK_PRIORITY"
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}TASK_PRIORITY@{ub}               Default:  TASK_PRIORITY=1


Priority of the TimeSignal task.

@ENDNODE


@NODE WaitForDCF77
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{B}WaitForDCF77@{UB}


Shell command. Waits for received time by DCF77.


@ENDNODE

@NODE WaitDCF77ifCrash
@SMARTWRAP
@{LINDENT 1}

@{B}WaitDCF77ifCrash@{UB}


Shell command. Waits for received time by DCF77 if the time of the battery backed up clock
has been corrupted by a software crash.

@ENDNODE

